## XBRL Primer

### Core Architecture

```
XBRL Ecosystem
|
+-- Taxonomy (the vocabulary — shared, standards-body maintained)
|   +-- Schema (.xsd)            Element definitions, data types, period types
|   +-- Calculation Linkbase     Arithmetic: parent = sum(weight * child)
|   +-- Presentation Linkbase    Statement hierarchy (indent structure, label roles)
|   +-- Label Linkbase           Human-readable names per element per label role
|   +-- Reference Linkbase       Links to ASC/IFRS authoritative literature
|   +-- Definition Linkbase      Dimensional relationships: axes, domains, hypercubes
|
+-- Instance Document (.xml for XBRL / .htm for iXBRL)
    +-- xbrli:xbrl root element
    +-- Contexts   (entity identifier + period + optional dimensional segment)
    +-- Units      (iso4217:USD, xbrli:shares, xbrli:pure)
    +-- Facts      (element qname + contextRef + unitRef + value + decimals)
```

### Taxonomy Layers: US-GAAP Filing Stack

```
Layer 1 (base):  XBRL 2.1 specification schemas
Layer 2:         US-GAAP 2024 taxonomy  (FASB, ~4,500 elements)
Layer 3:         DEI 2024 taxonomy      (SEC, entity/document metadata)
Layer 4:         SRT 2024 taxonomy      (SEC reporting taxonomy, dimensions)
Layer 5:         Company extension      (.xsd + 4 linkbases, custom elements only)
Layer 6:         Instance document      (facts referencing all layers above)

Every layer must resolve cleanly before instance validation proceeds.
Unresolvable schema imports = incomplete DTS = false-clean validation result.
```

